@startuml
title Kisan Sahayak - DFD Level 2 (Decomposition of 1.0 Crop Management & 5.0 AI Advisor)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 40
skinparam ranksep 40

' From Level 1: External inputs
actor Farmer
actor "Weather API" 
database "D1 User/Crop Data" as D1

' Level 2 Processes - decompose 1.0 Crop Management (1.1 - 1.4)
circle "1.1 Validate\nCrop Input" as P11
circle "1.2 Update\nGrowth Stage" as P12
circle "1.3 Calculate\nProgress %" as P13
circle "1.4 Generate\nAdvice Input" as P14

' Decompose 5.0 AI Advisor (5.1 - 5.3)
circle "5.1 Analyze\nCrop Data" as P51
circle "5.2 Language\nProcessing" as P52
circle "5.3 Advice\nGeneration" as P53

' Additional data stores for Level 2
database "D5 Growth\nRules" as D5
database "D6 AI\nKnowledge" as D6

' Flows for 1.0 decomposition
Farmer --> P11 : Crop name\ndate\narea
P11 --> P12 : Validated data
P12 <--> D5 : Growth rules
P12 --> D1 : Update crop stage
D1 --> P13 : Current progress
P13 --> P14 : % calculated
P14 --> P51 : Advice request

' Flows for 5.0 decomposition
P51 <--> D1 : Crop details
P51 <--> D6 : Knowledge base
P51 --> P52 : Processed data
P52 --> P53 : Localized text
P53 --> Farmer : Final advice/chat
Weather API --> P12 : Weather impact

note right of P11 : Validate wheat/maize etc.
note right of P12 : Stage: germination → harvest
note right of P13 : % based on days/weather
note right of P14 : Prepare AI input

note right of P51 : Risk analysis\nnutrient needs
note right of P52 : Hindi/English translation
note right of P53 : Natural language response

@enduml

Usage: Copy to https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml/
Level 2 focuses on detailed decomposition of key processes 1.0 and 5.0 from Level 1
